href="http://www.thingsaregood.com/2013/12/10/selling-sustainability-at-all-levels-of-a-company/" title="Permalink to Selling Sustainability at All Levels of a Company" rel="bookmark">Selling Sustainability at All Levels of a Company</a></h2><div
class="entry-meta"> <span
class="entry-date" title="2013/12/10 11:19 am"><a
href="http://www.thingsaregood.com/2013/12/10/selling-sustainability-at-all-levels-of-a-company/" title="Selling Sustainability at All Levels of a Company" rel="bookmark">2013/12/10 11:19 am</a></span><span
class="entry-meta-sep"> / </span><span
class="entry-author author vcard"><a
href="http://www.thingsaregood.com/author/administrator/" title="by Adam Clare" rel="author">Adam Clare</a></span></div><div
class="entry-content clearfix"><p>Every company ought to behave and operate in a sustainable way at all levels of operation. There is an obvious environmental argument for doing this, but some people don&#8217;t initially see the economic value. In this TED talk the economic efficiencies of sustainable manufacturing, distribution, and marketing are explored.</p><p><iframe
