id="post-3394" class="post-3394 post type-post status-publish format-standard hentry category-direct-action category-mind-space tag-film tag-meaning-of-life tag-video"><h2 class="entry-title"><a
href="http://www.thingsaregood.com/2012/08/02/crowdsourcing-the-meaning-of-life/" title="Permalink to Crowdsourcing the Meaning of Life" rel="bookmark">Crowdsourcing the Meaning of Life</a></h2><div
class="entry-meta"> <span
class="entry-date" title="2012/08/02 2:13 pm"><a
href="http://www.thingsaregood.com/2012/08/02/crowdsourcing-the-meaning-of-life/" title="Crowdsourcing the Meaning of Life" rel="bookmark">2012/08/02 2:13 pm</a></span><span
class="entry-meta-sep"> / </span><span
class="entry-author author vcard"><a
href="http://www.thingsaregood.com/author/administrator/" title="by Adam Clare" rel="author">Adam Clare</a></span></div><div
class="entry-content clearfix"><p>Some filmmakers are channelling the world to find out what the meaning of life is. Their project has started an <a
href="http://www.indiegogo.com/lifemeanswhat?a=451321">Indiegogo campaign</a> to fund their project and they can use your help.</p><p><iframe
width="560" height="315" src="http://www.youtube.com/embed/dxiVZwXLNOk" frameborder="0" allowfullscreen></iframe></p><blockquote><p>The world we live in is extremely confusing and precarious.  With economic meltdowns, global terrorism, ecological disasters, civil unrest, if we don&#8217;t find the answers now, there may soon be no life left to explore.  Simultaneously, it is an extremely exciting time and we now have the technological tools to communicate and collaborate to find solutions that have eluded us for millenia.  We are a group of award-winning filmmakers who believe in the power of the moving image to move the world, and we have initiated a crowdfunding campaign to launch a website &#8211; <a
href="http://lifemeanswhat.com">lifemeanswhat.com</a> &#8211; where we will create a tapestry of short films that will address meaning and purpose from a diverse array of perspectives, and provide in its patchwork a beautiful and profound reflection on life for all those who are looking to be entertained, inspired, and informed.</p></blockquote><p>Here&#8217;s a video they sent me about how much they like life:</p><p><iframe
width="560" height="315" src="http://www.youtube.com/embed/v6ibCYKjQTU" frameborder="0" allowfullscreen></iframe></p><div
class='sharedaddy sd-block sd-like jetpack-likes-widget-wrapper jetpack-likes-widget-unloaded' id='like-post-wrapper-1111807-3394-5383553d16521' data-src='//widgets.wp.com/likes/#blog_id=1111807&amp;post_id=3394&amp;origin=www.thingsaregood.com&amp;obj_id=1111807-3394-5383553d16521' data-name='like-post-frame-1111807-3394-5383553d16521'><h3 class='sd-title'>Like this:</h3><div
